1
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:35,020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:37,810
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:39,870
Be honest with me—

4
00:01:40,009 --> 00:01:41,450
in all the years we've known each other,

5
00:01:41,450 --> 00:01:42,780
have I ever scammed you?

6
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:43,310
No.

7
00:01:44,150 --> 00:01:45,680
Have I ever scammed

8
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,920
any of your friends?

9
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:47,920
No.

10
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:49,729
I'm reliable!

11
00:01:49,979 --> 00:01:51,110
You really haven't.

12
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:53,700
Wait a minute.

13
00:01:53,729 --> 00:01:54,930
I'll turn the TV down.

14
00:01:57,479 --> 00:01:58,120
Well...

15
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:00,160
Do you guys know

16
00:02:00,650 --> 00:02:02,480
how many people travel back and forth

17
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,180
between China and Russia

18
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,400
every year for trade?

19
00:02:05,650 --> 00:02:06,290
Do you know?

20
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:06,840
No.

21
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:08,440
100 thousand.

22
00:02:08,650 --> 00:02:10,050
Do you know how much money

23
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,850
these 100,000 people generate

24
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:12,800
in trade?

25
00:02:13,630 --> 00:02:14,410
We don't know that either.

26
00:02:14,410 --> 00:02:15,310
A billion or so?

27
00:02:15,970 --> 00:02:17,060
Forty billion.

28
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:18,960
Forty billion?

29
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:20,120
Do the math.

30
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,500
If you divide this 40 billion among these

31
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:22,190
100,000 people, how much

32
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:23,050
can each person make?

33
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:24,340
Seriously, if you go there now,

34
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:26,090
you could make money
with your eyes closed.

35
00:02:26,090 --> 00:02:27,250
Even if you don't,

36
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:29,490
just treat it as a trip.

37
00:02:29,579 --> 00:02:30,310
Go see Russia

38
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,120
and expand your horizons—

39
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,120
isn't that great?

40
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:35,360
Making money sounds great.

41
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,750
But if we go,

42
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,460
where will we live? Is it safe?

43
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:41,430
You'll definitely live better
than you do here.

44
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:43,560
At least it won't be a basement, right?

45
00:02:43,810 --> 00:02:45,079
It'll be clean and hygienic.

46
00:02:45,079 --> 00:02:46,210
I have a buddy there.

47
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:46,910
Everything

48
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,440
will be arranged properly.

49
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:49,190
How did you meet him?

50
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:49,970
During his attempt to chase you down?

51
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:51,740
Just shut up.

52
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:53,079
You don't know how to talk.

53
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:53,650
Jun.

54
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:54,780
If we go there,

55
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:56,510
how much can we make in one trip?

56
00:02:57,470 --> 00:02:59,600
The least I've made on my last few trips

57
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,860
was 5 or 6 thousand.

58
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,960
That much?

59
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:03,930
Dollars.

60
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:08,020
Shouldn't you earn rubles in Russia?

61
00:03:08,370 --> 00:03:09,310
You don't understand.

62
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:12,040
International trade,
international currency.

63
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:15,410
I do need money

64
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:16,900
to record backing tracks.

65
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:18,560
Don't we have backing tracks?

66
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:21,660
The teacher said
they need to be more professional.

67
00:03:22,210 --> 00:03:22,740
Buddy.

68
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:26,560
Looks like your two friends
are a little tempted.

69
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:29,870
Don't think about anything else.

70
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:30,870
Just work with me.

71
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,090
You can't always
spend your family's money.

72
00:03:33,090 --> 00:03:35,400
If I were spending my family's money,

73
00:03:36,130 --> 00:03:37,400
would I live here?

74
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,430
Well, you're not a little boy anymore.

75
00:03:40,430 --> 00:03:41,360
Don't you need to

76
00:03:41,370 --> 00:03:42,430
find a girlfriend?

77
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,190
Jun.

78
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:48,930
Did he...

79
00:03:50,570 --> 00:03:52,370
You just went through a breakup?

80
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:55,960
That makes it even better.

81
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,840
You need to make money even more now.

82
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,560
Think about it.

83
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,020
What do young girls want these days?

84
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:00,430
Right?

85
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,900
Are they after your looks?

86
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:02,500
Unlikely.

87
00:04:02,620 --> 00:04:03,680
You look a bit goofy.

88
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,870
not even as good-looking as me.

89
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:07,080
They want a sense of security.

90
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,710
That girl definitely ran off with someone

91
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,620
because of money.

92
00:04:09,620 --> 00:04:10,620
You should just make money.

93
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:12,090
Make as much as you can and piss her off.

94
00:04:12,090 --> 00:04:12,580
I'll do it.

95
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:13,030
Do it!

96
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,210
It's just my life.

97
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:14,640
Right!

98
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:15,310
I'll do it!

99
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:17,630
I'll come back driving a fancy car too.

100
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:18,890
Then the two of us will go too.

101
00:04:18,890 --> 00:04:20,490
It's safer with more people.

102
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:21,540
Yeah, if the four of us go together,

103
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:22,060
we can carry more goods

104
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:23,460
on the way there and back.

105
00:04:23,810 --> 00:04:25,140
I'm the oldest among us.

106
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:26,480
Let me get this out of the way first.

107
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,950
Even brothers
must settle accounts clearly.

108
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:28,620
We'll split the profit

109
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:30,800
based on how much money we put in, okay?

110
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,450
Okay.

111
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,270
How much will you put in?

112
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:34,770
I'll put in 2,000.

113
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:35,620
And you?

114
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:37,500
Then I'll put in 1,000.

115
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:38,600
The two of us count as one.

116
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,260
It's 3,000.

117
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:39,810
Okay.

118
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:42,400
How much will you put in?

119
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:43,560
I'll put in 900.

120
00:04:43,690 --> 00:04:45,130
Is it enough to buy a train ticket?

121
00:04:45,130 --> 00:04:45,830
Of course.

122
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,600
Those who put in more get more,

123
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,420
those who put in less get less.

124
00:04:48,420 --> 00:04:49,680
But it doesn't matter.

125
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:51,950
The important thing is that
we're doing this together!

126
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:52,750
Come on, Jun.

127
00:04:52,810 --> 00:04:53,610
A toast to you.

128
00:04:54,430 --> 00:04:55,060
Come on.

129
00:04:55,890 --> 00:04:57,620
I wonder if you enjoyed the meal.

130
00:04:57,620 --> 00:04:58,870
We did.

131
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:00,270
Let's meet again some other time.

132
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,390
Okay.

133
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,680
Mr. Chu is waiting for you?

134
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,010
Oh, this child.

135
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:16,120
If I had known you found

136
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:17,340
someone like Mr. Chu,

137
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,930
why would I have introduced

138
00:05:18,930 --> 00:05:20,060
this classmate to you?

139
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:21,320
You didn't even ask

140
00:05:21,370 --> 00:05:22,370
how old he is

141
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:24,420
or about his family background.

142
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:27,740
What does his age matter?

143
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,280
Didn't you say

144
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:32,430
as long as he can handle the thing
in Beijing,

145
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:33,360
it would be fine?

146
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,360
Alright.

147
00:05:36,159 --> 00:05:36,860
I'm going back

148
00:05:36,860 --> 00:05:38,930
to pack your luggage.

149
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:42,320
Mr. Chu!

150
00:05:42,890 --> 00:05:44,860
I won't bother you guys.

151
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:47,430
Goodbye.

152
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:57,540
Sorry about that.

153
00:05:57,870 --> 00:05:59,200
My mom is just like that.

154
00:05:59,420 --> 00:06:01,060
What's there to be sorry about?

155
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:02,460
I think she's quite nice.

156
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,240
Oh, right.

157
00:06:04,310 --> 00:06:05,720
I already booked the flight tickets.

158
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,130
It's from Hangzhou to Beijing.

159
00:06:07,130 --> 00:06:08,590
If you're eager to return,

160
00:06:08,890 --> 00:06:09,870
we can fly back.

161
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:10,810
Otherwise,

162
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:12,560
I have another suggestion.

163
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,020
I want to return to Beijing

164
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:16,120
and Seasons Change Hostel
as soon as possible.

165
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:16,810
Thank you.

166
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:18,990
Then we will take the flight.

167
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,710
Don't go. Just stay at home.

168
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,270
I don't want to hear any sounds.

169
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:41,000
I just want to live

170
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,770
like this every day.

171
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:49,980
I don't want to go either.

172
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,390
I also want to

173
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:55,930
be with my wife and kid every day.

174
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,520
But I'm halfway through this.

175
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,620
If you make me stop,

176
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:00,800
I'll feel bad.

177
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,220
A family of three is complete

178
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:06,930
and content.

179
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,890
Give me one more year. Just one year.

180
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,160
Just one year?

181
00:07:15,690 --> 00:07:16,450
One year.

182
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:47,450
Cao Ye.

183
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:51,950
Cao Ye.

184
00:07:57,950 --> 00:07:58,500
Cao Ye.

185
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,120
Cao Ye!

186
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:24,980
Dad.

187
00:08:26,450 --> 00:08:27,710
I went back to Beijing.

188
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:30,780
The lanterns have been painted.

189
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:33,240
But I won't paint anymore.

190
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:34,470
I'm tired.

191
00:08:35,909 --> 00:08:37,510
I should have listened to you

192
00:08:37,630 --> 00:08:39,030
and been more practical.

193
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:40,980
As for dreams,

194
00:08:41,549 --> 00:08:43,740
some people can reach them
just by standing on tiptoe,

195
00:08:43,740 --> 00:08:46,670
while others
can never touch them in their lifetime.

196
00:08:48,940 --> 00:08:49,220
Dad,

197
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:51,280
only money

198
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,480
can make it so we

199
00:08:52,510 --> 00:08:55,110
no longer have to look
at other people's faces.

200
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:57,180
Dad,

201
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,520
I've decided to change my way of living.

202
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:01,870
Wait for my good news.

203
00:09:12,130 --> 00:09:12,860
Ranran?

204
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:16,160
Northeasterner? Happy New Year.

205
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,240
Happy New Year. Happy New Year.

206
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,630
Why are you back so early?

207
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:19,890
I missed you guys.

208
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,030
You missed us?

209
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,580
Train tickets to Beijing

210
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:25,250
are hard to buy now.

211
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:26,290
How did you get one?

212
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:27,690
I asked a friend for help.

213
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,750
Your friend must be pretty capable.

214
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,270
Where are they?

215
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,320
Are they back?

216
00:09:33,890 --> 00:09:35,290
You mean Tao Liangliang?

217
00:09:35,340 --> 00:09:36,540
I mean Zhuang Zhuang.

218
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,240
Zhuang Zhuang, Liangliang,

219
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,030
and Xu Shengli.

220
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:40,910
The three of them

221
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:42,970
went off with a scalper from Beijing.

222
00:09:43,630 --> 00:09:44,550
Where did they go?

223
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:45,250
Russia.

224
00:09:46,770 --> 00:09:48,180
Why did they go to Russia?

225
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,000
To make money, of course.

226
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:50,650
Do you think

227
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:52,180
they went to Russia for fun?

228
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:53,200
Let me tell you,

229
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,660
anyone who knows anything

230
00:09:54,820 --> 00:09:55,840
knows that

231
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,640
reselling in Russia isn't easy.

232
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,650
Take a rest.

233
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:14,270
I'm fine.

234
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:16,100
Jun.

235
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:19,220
My back is breaking.

236
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:22,360
I paid for this train ticket.

237
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,310
I wanted to get some solid sleep.

238
00:10:24,410 --> 00:10:24,840
Now,

239
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:26,840
I haven't had a good sleep in three days.

240
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,630
Have a seat.

241
00:10:27,630 --> 00:10:28,800
It's fine. Go ahead.

242
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:29,550
Hurry.

243
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:32,630
I can't straighten my back

244
00:10:32,630 --> 00:10:34,080
or my legs.

245
00:10:36,460 --> 00:10:37,600
When will we arrive?

246
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:40,610
Jun?

247
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:42,710
I only slept for a short while.

248
00:10:42,860 --> 00:10:44,060
Keep your mouth shut.

249
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,150
We'll be there soon.

250
00:10:45,150 --> 00:10:46,150
You talk too much.

251
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,080
We haven't arrived yet,

252
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,200
and we can't go back either.

253
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,530
If you throw me out of the train,

254
00:10:50,530 --> 00:10:52,100
I wouldn't even know where I am.

255
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,030
I can't even sleep.

256
00:10:53,030 --> 00:10:53,530
Right now,

257
00:10:53,530 --> 00:10:54,890
I'm sleeping here

258
00:10:54,890 --> 00:10:56,090
with a bunch of sacks.

259
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:57,240
You are really...

260
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,040
How could I...

261
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,360
bring you out?

262
00:10:59,410 --> 00:11:00,630
These sacks are almost pushing me

263
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:01,870
off the bed.

264
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,290
Th-The place you're at now

265
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:05,050
is... is called Blagoveshchensk.

266
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:06,240
Do you know where it is?

267
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,320
Do you understand now that I've told you?

268
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,620
Just take a nap.

269
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:10,280
We still have work to do later.

270
00:11:10,790 --> 00:11:12,060
Be careful.

271
00:11:12,290 --> 00:11:12,960
Come on. M-

272
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:14,100
Me? Be careful?

273
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,900
I have more than 10 sacks up here.

274
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:18,510
When have I ever suffered like this?

275
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:22,180
Hurry up

276
00:11:22,530 --> 00:11:23,650
and cut the crap.

277
00:11:24,170 --> 00:11:25,150
Get some sleep

278
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,320
to save your energy.

279
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,650
-We have work to do.
-There are eggs.

280
00:11:27,650 --> 00:11:28,290
Get an egg.

281
00:11:28,370 --> 00:11:29,150
How can I sleep?

282
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,720
It's full of luggage up here.

283
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,640
There's no room for me at all.

284
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:33,720
Then don't sleep.

285
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:35,910
I was thinking of

286
00:11:36,010 --> 00:11:36,910
taking you out to have fun.

287
00:11:36,910 --> 00:11:37,770
I didn't expect

288
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:40,130
that it would turn into a cargo run.

289
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:42,000
We came out
to do business in the first place.

290
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,440
It's already good enough.

291
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,600
These instant noodles are so delicious.

292
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:45,130
You eat.

293
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:06,000
Stop sleeping! Stop sleeping!

294
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:06,910
There's going to be a war!

295
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:07,740
There's going to be a war!

296
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:08,720
Listen to my command.

297
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:11,100
Your eyes must be sharp,
your hands must be fast,

298
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:12,240
and your legs must be diligent. Got it?

299
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:12,770
Later...

300
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,690
My legs are numb.

301
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:15,370
Let's go. Let's go.

302
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:16,480
-What's happening?
-Get off! Get off!

303
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,010
Well, give me what...

304
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:20,280
Give me what I tell you to give me!

305
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:32,870
Excuse me!

306
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:33,600
Excuse me!

307
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,100
Open the window! Open the window!

308
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,100
Here, let me do it!

309
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:37,750
Open the window! Open the window!

310
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,150
That one! I want that one!

311
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:42,630
Right away!

312
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:46,600
Three hundred a sack!
Three hundred a sack!

313
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,320
Good stuff!

314
00:12:48,010 --> 00:12:49,050
Good stuff!

315
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:49,940
Good stuff!

316
00:12:56,740 --> 00:12:59,070
Take whichever you like!

317
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:00,530
Take whichever you like!

318
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:03,320
Good stuff!

319
00:13:04,370 --> 00:13:05,220
Careful! Careful!

320
00:13:05,220 --> 00:13:05,890
Take a look!

321
00:13:52,850 --> 00:13:53,530
Jun.

322
00:13:53,890 --> 00:13:55,080
Get some sleep after you eat,

323
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,140
and get a good rest.

324
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,580
You guys should eat something quickly

325
00:13:58,580 --> 00:13:59,170
to regain your energy.

326
00:13:59,170 --> 00:14:00,500
There are 2 stops ahead.

327
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:03,030
He's yelled himself hoarse.

328
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:04,530
This trip is like fighting a war.

329
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:06,530
I've never seen anything like this.

330
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,150
Money was falling like rain,

331
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,670
just pouring down.

332
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:10,750
It was unbelievable.

333
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:11,840
As the saying goes,

334
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:14,520
"Time is money." Right?

335
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:15,270
Look.

336
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:15,840
We've verified that

337
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:16,650
time is money.

338
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,770
We just earned all this.

339
00:14:19,010 --> 00:14:20,320
Let's count it out by our shares

340
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,220
and split it.

341
00:14:21,910 --> 00:14:23,640
We're splitting it right here?

342
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:25,290
Right here.

343
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:27,080
We split it every time we earn a batch,

344
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,810
so we don't get confused later.

345
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,980
It was such a short while

346
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:32,270
and we earned this much.

347
00:14:32,270 --> 00:14:33,870
We're not even in Moscow yet.

348
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:37,000
You can count on Mr. Lucky for good luck.

349
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,500
We'll earn money from here to Moscow,

350
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,430
and then earn more all the way back.

351
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,030
Jun, if I had known it would be like this,

352
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:42,870
I would have asked

353
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:44,100
all my relatives

354
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:46,770
to borrow money to invest in this.

355
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,300
Regret it now, huh?

356
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:51,210
You only paid for your train tickets.

357
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:52,600
You should have put in more money.

358
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,440
Remember what I said earlier

359
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,240
about the three key points?

360
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:54,970
Repeat them.

361
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:57,250
Your eyes must be sharp,
your hands must be fast...

362
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:59,130
Your eyes must be sharp,
your hands must be fast,

363
00:14:59,130 --> 00:14:59,720
and your legs must be diligent.

364
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:00,120
Right.

365
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,370
Sharp, fast and diligent.

366
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:02,770
Remember these three points.

367
00:15:02,770 --> 00:15:04,500
The four of us will work together as one,

368
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:06,300
charge forward, and make money!

369
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,620
We will make a fortune!

370
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:08,720
We will make a fortune!

371
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:09,980
We will make a fortune!

372
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:12,180
Let me take a sip.

373
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,340
Take it. Here.

374
00:15:14,030 --> 00:15:14,770
Let me take a sip.

375
00:15:14,770 --> 00:15:15,910
Eat something too. Get some energy.

376
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,050
I'm starving, really.

377
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:17,940
There are eggs.

378
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:18,530
There are eggs.

379
00:15:18,530 --> 00:15:19,630
-In that blue bag.
-Where are the eggs?

380
00:15:19,630 --> 00:15:20,790
-The blue bag?
-Yes.

381
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:23,860
Why didn't you say
there were eggs earlier?

382
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:29,660
[Moscow]

383
00:15:57,770 --> 00:15:58,570
Wait a moment.

384
00:15:58,890 --> 00:16:00,420
The train is arriving soon.

385
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:01,260
Jun.

386
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,630
Did we sell all our big and small sacks

387
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:04,130
on the train?

388
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,270
Six days on the train

389
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,340
made each of us ten thousand?

390
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:08,490
That's awesome.

391
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:09,710
A scalper

392
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:11,200
means you can make money

393
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:11,860
both going and returning.

394
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:12,790
That's called a scalper.

395
00:16:12,790 --> 00:16:14,240
Playing that crappy saxophone of yours—

396
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,340
only exhaling without inhaling—

397
00:16:15,340 --> 00:16:16,170
how's that supposed to work?

398
00:16:16,170 --> 00:16:17,710
We profit both ways.

399
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:18,890
You're really good at doing business.

400
00:16:18,890 --> 00:16:20,220
Now that they're all sold out,

401
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:21,270
what do we sell?

402
00:16:21,740 --> 00:16:22,340
My

403
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,550
big brain

404
00:16:23,550 --> 00:16:24,610
is full of wisdom.

405
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:25,750
Before coming here,

406
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,080
I had my buddy in Beijing

407
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:29,070
send a batch of goods over.

408
00:16:29,070 --> 00:16:30,630
Jeans and thermal underwear.

409
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:31,500
We just need to pick them up.

410
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:32,250
Then when we came here,

411
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:34,050
why didn't we bring them with us?

412
00:16:34,460 --> 00:16:35,620
Even with four of us,

413
00:16:35,650 --> 00:16:36,840
we still couldn't carry them all.

414
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:37,530
For such a large batch of goods,

415
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:38,550
we need a truck.

416
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:40,250
I figured we shouldn't come empty-handed.

417
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:40,600
Right?

418
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,320
On the way back and forth,

419
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,460
we can just carry some stuff to sell.

420
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:42,980
Once we get off the train,

421
00:16:42,980 --> 00:16:44,510
we'll sell the large batch.

422
00:16:44,650 --> 00:16:46,130
Will we still sell at the train station?

423
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:46,710
No.

424
00:16:46,790 --> 00:16:48,080
We need to go to the big market.

425
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,500
In Russia, there are special

426
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,150
big markets provided for Chinese

427
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:52,370
to sell goods

428
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:53,140
to Russians.

429
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:55,440
Only those big markets
can bring in big money.

430
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,410
You three have to make a decision.

431
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,130
Do you want to come here

432
00:16:59,130 --> 00:16:59,990
just to travel,

433
00:17:00,010 --> 00:17:02,170
or follow Mr. Lucky to try your luck—

434
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:03,460
put in the little money you earned

435
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:05,250
and let's make big money together?

436
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,569
Of course we'll keep doing it.

437
00:17:06,569 --> 00:17:08,829
Who wouldn't want to make big money
with little money?

438
00:17:08,829 --> 00:17:09,829
We're all in.

439
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:12,339
Let's do it.
Treat it as experiencing life.

440
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:13,530
Doing business here,

441
00:17:13,530 --> 00:17:14,810
you all need to be careful.

442
00:17:14,810 --> 00:17:16,000
There are all kinds of people.

443
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,950
And some will scam anyone.

444
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:19,790
We made it here

445
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,109
safely.

446
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,250
As the oldest among us,

447
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:23,310
I'm responsible for getting all of us

448
00:17:23,310 --> 00:17:24,490
back safely.

449
00:17:24,589 --> 00:17:25,430
Understood?

450
00:17:25,609 --> 00:17:26,420
Whatever you do,

451
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,140
be extremely careful.

452
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:29,860
Follow my lead.

453
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:31,750
My throat is really giving out.

454
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,350
I'll buy a Kvass to soothe it.

455
00:17:34,070 --> 00:17:35,000
Stay close to me.

456
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:38,810
Let's go. Hurry up.

457
00:17:38,810 --> 00:17:39,480
Let's go.

458
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:44,990
We're here.

459
00:17:45,550 --> 00:17:46,610
Sir, please wait a moment.

460
00:17:46,610 --> 00:17:47,850
We need to get our luggage.

461
00:17:47,850 --> 00:17:49,070
This is my friend's house.

462
00:17:49,070 --> 00:17:50,800
It's cheaper than hotel rooms.

463
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,090
The environment is nice,

464
00:17:52,090 --> 00:17:54,020
and it's comfortable to stay here.

465
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:55,940
Although it's a bit far from the city,

466
00:17:55,940 --> 00:17:56,660
we can borrow this car

467
00:17:56,660 --> 00:17:57,770
every now and then

468
00:17:57,940 --> 00:17:59,180
to carry some goods or something.

469
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,180
It's pretty good.

470
00:18:00,460 --> 00:18:01,380
Sophia!

471
00:18:01,510 --> 00:18:02,810
This house is pretty nice.

472
00:18:02,810 --> 00:18:03,460
It looks so big.

473
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:04,680
-Sophia!
-It's quite pretty.

474
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,020
Sophia!

475
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:08,200
Jun!

476
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:11,460
Sophia, Sophia, Sophia!

477
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,120
We meet again!

478
00:18:16,650 --> 00:18:17,710
Let me kiss you too.

479
00:18:24,010 --> 00:18:26,050
-It's cold. Get in.
-Let's go inside.

480
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:27,460
How have you been lately?

481
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,590
I'm doing well.

482
00:18:28,590 --> 00:18:30,520
It's been so long since we last met.

483
00:18:30,830 --> 00:18:31,290
Well...

484
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:34,360
Should we go in now?

485
00:18:34,810 --> 00:18:36,350
The thing is, we don't even know

486
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:38,440
what the situation is right now.

487
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:41,460
Here.

488
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:42,200
Have some tea.

489
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,000
Hello. Hello.

490
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:44,320
Hello.

491
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:46,270
Don't...

492
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,810
Don't trouble yourself.

493
00:18:47,810 --> 00:18:50,270
Pour it yourself if you want some.
It's fine.

494
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,620
Let me introduce you.

495
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,380
Sophia.

496
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,420
She is...

497
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:03,310
is... is my best friend.

498
00:19:03,460 --> 00:19:04,990
We're really really close.

499
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:06,810
Jun...

500
00:19:07,530 --> 00:19:09,790
Then why did you kiss each other just now?

501
00:19:10,180 --> 00:19:11,350
That was etiquette.

502
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:12,140
Do you understand?

503
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:13,110
It's local etiquette.

504
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:13,830
Hillbilly.

505
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,560
Um... This is Shengli.

506
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:18,790
-Hello.
-And Zhuang Zhuang.

507
00:19:18,790 --> 00:19:19,240
Hello.

508
00:19:19,350 --> 00:19:21,080
Jun. He's my childhood friend.

509
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,640
My name is not Jun.

510
00:19:22,950 --> 00:19:24,440
It's Liangliang.
Liangliang is my childhood friend.

511
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:24,980
You don't understand.

512
00:19:24,980 --> 00:19:25,850
I'll explain it to you later.

513
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:27,680
And this time,

514
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:28,550
I brought them along

515
00:19:28,550 --> 00:19:29,570
to see the world.

516
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:32,220
And to make some money together.

517
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:32,920
Hello, Sister-in-law.

518
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:33,640
Hello.

519
00:19:34,510 --> 00:19:35,270
Jun's friends

520
00:19:35,270 --> 00:19:36,630
are my friends.

521
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:39,400
Welcome to Russia.

522
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,330
Your Chinese is so good.

523
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,790
Her Chinese is very good.

524
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:43,310
Sit.

525
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:44,370
Let's sit and talk.

526
00:19:45,530 --> 00:19:46,840
No... It's fine.

527
00:19:46,980 --> 00:19:47,980
It's fine. I can just

528
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:48,910
tell you

529
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:49,750
how I

530
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,440
met Sophia.

531
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:53,700
Relax. Just relax.

532
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:55,000
I am relaxed.

533
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,570
What are you saying?

534
00:19:57,010 --> 00:19:57,810
I was...

535
00:19:58,790 --> 00:19:59,640
Well... At first,

536
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:00,770
I came

537
00:20:00,770 --> 00:20:02,090
to Russia alone to do business.

538
00:20:02,090 --> 00:20:02,920
I was new here

539
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,610
and unfamiliar with the place.

540
00:20:04,610 --> 00:20:05,350
That day, I happened to be stopped

541
00:20:05,350 --> 00:20:06,210
for an ID check,

542
00:20:06,420 --> 00:20:07,240
and I didn't have my ID with me.

543
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,710
I couldn't explain myself clearly

544
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:09,920
and ended up gesturing a lot.

545
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,160
They didn't know what I was doing,

546
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,810
and insisted on taking me away.

547
00:20:12,810 --> 00:20:15,590
Right at the moment
they were about to take me away,

548
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:16,290
I heard

549
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:17,590
a heavenly voice—

550
00:20:21,850 --> 00:20:23,200
"What are you doing?

551
00:20:23,610 --> 00:20:24,850
I can speak Chinese."

552
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,400
When I turned around,

553
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,260
I saw Sophia standing against the light.

554
00:20:29,260 --> 00:20:31,060
The sunlight was shining on her,

555
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:32,330
golden and bright,

556
00:20:32,350 --> 00:20:33,610
like an angel

557
00:20:34,010 --> 00:20:35,210
descending to earth.

558
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:37,440
She spoke in her standard Mandarin

559
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:38,110
and saved my life.

560
00:20:38,110 --> 00:20:39,000
Now, whenever I talk about it—

561
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,500
look—I get goosebumps.

562
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:41,990
Thank you. Thank you.

563
00:20:42,830 --> 00:20:45,090
This story deserves a round of applause.

564
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,690
I run a

565
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,050
handicraft business in Russia.

566
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:53,110
After I met Jun,

567
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:54,250
I started selling

568
00:20:54,530 --> 00:20:56,050
my crafts to China.

569
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:57,610
So knowing him

570
00:20:57,610 --> 00:20:58,770
is truly my luck.

571
00:20:59,460 --> 00:21:01,480
Meeting you is also my luck

572
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,410
for 8 lifetimes.

573
00:21:02,810 --> 00:21:04,670
My ancestors must be blessing me.

574
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,790
Didn't you say

575
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:12,160
you love Chinese tea?

576
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,480
I asked someone
to get this specially for you.

577
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:16,770
Yunnan Dahongpao.

578
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:18,710
And Maojian. It's green tea.

579
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:19,800
[Tea]

580
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:19,770
And this.

581
